<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://xamarin.com/schemas/2014/forms"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="LearningApp.View.Module4Page" Title="Module 4">
    <ContentPage.Content>
        <ScrollView>
            <StackLayout>
                <StackLayout>
                    <Label Text="Module 4: Loops"
                           Padding="20,30,20,0"
                           FontSize="30"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand" />
                </StackLayout>
                <StackLayout x:Name="ModuleCourseContent">
                        <Label 
                           Padding="20,20,10,10"
                           FontSize="Body"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                            <x:String>
                                There are two types of loops in Python, for and while.
                            </x:String>
                        </Label>
                </StackLayout>
                <StackLayout Padding="20,0,20,10">
                    <WebView VerticalOptions="FillAndExpand"
                        HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand"
                        Source="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6iF8Xb7Z3wQ"
                        WidthRequest="500"
                        HeightRequest="200"
                        IsVisible="true"/>
                </StackLayout>
                 <StackLayout>
                    <Label Text="The for loop"
                           Padding="20,0,20,0"
                           FontSize="20"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand" />
                </StackLayout>

                 <StackLayout x:Name="ForExample">
                        <Label 
                           Padding="20,0,10,10"
                           FontSize="Body"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                            <x:String>
For loops iterate over a given sequence. Here is an example:
primes = [2, 3, 5, 7]
for prime in primes:
    print(prime)
                            </x:String>
                        </Label>
                </StackLayout>
                                 <StackLayout>
                    <Label Text="The while loop"
                           Padding="20,0,20,0"
                           FontSize="20"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand" />
                </StackLayout>

                 <StackLayout x:Name="WhileExample">
                        <Label 
                           Padding="20,0,10,10"
                           FontSize="Body"
                           VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand"
                           HorizontalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                            <x:String>
While loops repeat as long as a certain boolean condition is met.
count = 0
while count &#60; 5:
    print(count)
    count += 1 # This is the same as count = count +
                            </x:String>
                        </Label>
                </StackLayout>
                <StackLayout x:Name="QuizButton">
                    <Button Text="Start Quiz"
                            CornerRadius="20"
                            Clicked="redirectToQuiz"
                            Margin="20,0,20,10" />
                </StackLayout>
            </StackLayout>
        </ScrollView>
    </ContentPage.Content>
</ContentPage>